cquisitionsedit when the state of texas deregulated the electricity market the former houston lighting  power hlp was split into several companies in  hlp was split into texas genco which got the power plants centerpoint energy which got the distribution system and reliant energy which provided the electricity to business and individuals in  nrg energy bought texas genco from a group of private equity firms for roughly  billion afterwards in may  nrg energy acquired the retail operations of reliant energy with those two moves nrgs holdings represented most of the former hlp and today serve  million customers in texas the retail operations continue to operate under the reliant energy name while the remainder of the former reliant energy became rri energy following the acquisition of reliant nrg extended its retail footprint with the acquisition of green mountain energy in november  in doing so nrg also became the largest retailer of green power in the nation providing all of its green mountain and many of its reliant customers with energy derived from  renewable resources nrg energy completed its acquisition of genon energy in december  for  billion in stock and cash the genon name was retired in the merger but the combined company retained genons houston headquarters to coordinate operations in august  nrg acquired energy curtailment specialists a buffalo new york based demand response company the terms of the deal were not disclosed  a goal zero battery lamp and solar panel in september  nrg acquired goal zero a manufacturer of personal solar power products naming rightsedit nrg energy holds the naming rights to the nrg park campus in houston texas home to the nrg astrodome nrg stadium nrg arena and nrg center on march   nrg energy announced that they would be rebranding reliant park to replace reliant on all signages to nrg wholesale generationedit after the genon merger nrg has  mw of total generation capacity enough to power approximately  million homes its nearly  power plants are located in  states in the northeast chicago area gulf coast southwest nevada and california generation facilities include mostly fossil fuel power plants powered by natural gas oil and coal plus four wind farms in texas and six solar farms in california arizona and new mexico nrg also has a  ownership stake in the south texas nuclear generating station and a  stake in a coal power plant in gladstone queensland australia some facilities use cogeneration and the company also owns mw of solar distributed generation retail electricityedit nrgs retail power services provide electricity services to more than  million homes and businesses mostly in arizona and the northeastcitation needed green energy initiativesedit nissan leaf recharging from an evgo network charging station in houston texas beginning in  nrg began an initiative to become an green energy producer in the united states and started investing money in clean energy projects they include onshore and offshore wind power solar thermal energy photovoltaic and distributed solar power facilities and repowering of some of their traditional coal plants with biomass in late  nrg launched the evgo network the first completely private public car charging station network for electric power vehicles the company signed a twoyear agreement beginning in january  to provide  renewable energy for the empire state building assemblywoman aravella simotas has been chair of a coalition to support the utility in their plan to replace its decadesold dirty power plant in astoria with a newer generator the company stated its intention in  to replace  older oil generators with new gas generators that will increase the megawatts of power while reducing emissions see alsoedit new jersey portal new york portal houston portal energy portal renewable energy portal nuclear technology portal companies portal greenstreet nrg tower new york energy law referencesedit  a b c d nrg and genon complete merger creating nation’s largest competitive power generator business wire press release retrieved    a b nrg energy inc annual report form k united states securities and exchange commission february     a b c nrg energy inc annual report form k united states securities and exchange commission february     httpwwwnjcommercerindexssfwestwindsorofficialstoutsustainabilityelementsofnrgenergysnewmheadquartershtmlincartriver  httpwwwnjcommercerindexssfofficialsbreakgroundonnrgenergysnewheadquartersinwestwindsorhtmlincartriver  contact us nrg energy retrieved on july    carnegie center princeton nj   township of west windsor new jersey zoning map township of west windsor retrieved on july    exit revisited nrg energy inc  exelon bids for major texas power producer nrg houston chronicle october   retrieved on april   the plants were originally part of the former houston lighting  power the integrated utility that served the houston area until it was broken up into three separate companies as the state deregulated its power markets  fowler tom  houston power plants to be sold to nrg houston chronicle october   retrieved on april    sec form k accession no   green mountain energy to be acquired for  million    nrg completes acquisition of green mountain energy  nrg energy to buy genon for  billion  nrg acquires energy curtailment specialists  nrg acquires energy curtailment specialists works with thinkeco  httpwwwrechargenewscomsolarnrgsealsgoalzeroacquisition  a b a new st century energy company retrieved    a b c generation assets pdf retrieved    a b httpnrgenergycom  httpswwwnytimescombusinessenergyenvironmentnrgsetsgoalstocutcarbonemissionshtml  evgo retrieved  june    empire state building to purchase  renewable power january     green mountain signs up new yorks empire state building  a b trapasso clare may   nrg hopes to replace  generators in astoria new york daily news retrieved october     henely rebecca april   officials support astoria repowering to grow jobs times ledger retrieved octob