n energy in november  in doing so nrg also became the largest retailer of green power in the nation providing all of its green mountain and many of its reliant customers with energy derived from  renewable resources nrg energy completed its acquisition of genon energy in december  for  billion in stock and cash the genon name was retired in the merger but the combined company retained genons houston headquarters to coordinate operations in august  nrg acquired energy curtailment specialists a buffalo new york based demand response company the terms of the deal were not disclosed  a goal zero battery lamp and solar panel in september  nrg acquired goal zero a manufacturer of personal solar power products naming rightsedit nrg energy holds the naming rights to the nrg park campus in houston texas home to the nrg astrodome nrg stadium nrg arena and nrg center on march   nrg energy announced that they would be rebranding reliant park to replace reliant on all signages to nrg wholesale generationedit after the genon merger nrg has  mw of total generation capacity enough to power approximately  million homes its nearly  power plants are located in  states in the northeast chicago area gulf coast southwest nevada and california generation facilities include mostly fossil fuel power plants powered by natural gas oil and coal plus four wind farms in texas and six solar farms in california arizona and new mexico nrg also has a  ownership stake in the south texas nuclear generating station and a  stake in a coal power plant in gladstone queensland australia some facilities use cogeneration and the company also owns mw of solar distributed generation retail electricityedit nrgs retail power services provide electricity services to more than  million homes and businesses mostly in arizona and the northeastcitation needed green energy initiativesedit nissan leaf recharging from an evgo network charging station in houston texas beginning in  nrg began an initiative to become an gr